119.0	Chinua_Achebe	Chinua Achebe	Albert Chinụalụmọgụ Achebe (born 16 November 1930) popularly known as Chinua Achebe ( ) is a Nigerian novelist, poet, professor, and critic. He is best known for his first novel and magnum opus, Things Fall Apart (1958), which is the most widely read book in modern African literature.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ef/Chinua_Achebe_-_Buffalo_25Sep2008_crop.jpg/200px-Chinua_Achebe_-_Buffalo_25Sep2008_crop.jpg
